@startuml sequence-htmx-render
title The rendering contract: server renders DOM, Alpine reacts, HTMX moves

actor User
participant "Browser DOM\n(PatternFly markup)" as DOM
participant "HTMX" as HTMX
participant "Alpine.js" as Alpine
participant "JAX-RS route\n(consumer app)" as Route
participant "Typed model /\ntemplate data" as Model
participant "Qute engine\n(component fragment)" as Qute

User -> DOM : click / input / scroll
DOM -> HTMX : hx-get / hx-post trigger
HTMX -> Route : HTTP request (fragment URL)
Route -> Model : build typed component model
Route -> Qute : render component template with model
Qute --> Route : HTML fragment (final DOM,\nx-data attributes inline)
Route --> HTMX : 200 text/html
HTMX -> DOM : hx-swap (replace target subtree)
DOM -> Alpine : new subtree scanned
Alpine -> DOM : hydrate x-data state,\nlocal reactivity only
note right of Qute
  JSON never becomes HTML
  in the browser — the server
  always renders the DOM.
end note
@enduml
